<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Samsung dryer jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Samsung dryer service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Samsung DV45R6100EW electric, Sherman Oaks</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dryer running normal cycles but clothes coming out damp. Owner had run the same load through twice and still ended up partially wet.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Heating element ohms-out tested 12% above spec, early-stage burnout. Vent inspection: partial lint accumulation at the exterior wall cap (typical of 18+ months without vent cleaning). Thermal fuse tested fine but the element was clearly the primary issue, with the partial vent restriction accelerating element wear.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Heating element replacement with OEM Samsung part (in stock on the truck). Full vent run cleaning included as same-trip work. Verified normal exhaust airflow and complete drying on test cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $385 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 90 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Samsung DVG50R5400W gas, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> HE error code at startup, dryer wouldn't run any cycle. Owner had reset the dryer and the code returned within 60 seconds.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Vent inspection showed clear airflow at exterior cap. Gas valve coil test: one of the two coils ohms-out reading open, coil burned out. Gas igniter and flame sensor tested fine. HE was triggered by the no-heat condition rather than overheating in this case.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Gas valve coil set replacement (Samsung sells coils as a paired set for proper sequencing) with OEM part. Verified normal ignition sequence, full heating, HE cleared on test cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, 80 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Samsung DV50T5300EW electric, Newport Beach</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Loud high-pitched squeak from the dryer at the start of every cycle, getting louder over the past 6 weeks. Cycle complete normally; just the noise was the complaint.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Squeak isolated to the idler pulley, tested by manually rotating the drum with belt removed (silent) vs. with belt installed (squeak reproduced). Drum support rollers tested fine, no rumble. Year 6 unit consistent with idler pulley typical wear window.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Idler pulley + drum belt replacement with OEM Samsung parts (in stock). Replaced as paired set per standard practice, old belt with new pulley fails again within months. Verified silent operation on full cycle test.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, 65 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
